instruction: Please analyze the MSCI Japan Governance Quality index between 2010 and June of this year and explain its relation to Prime Minister Abe's corporate reform agenda.
output: According to the MSCI Japan Governance Quality index, which is the blue-green line in the graph, Japanese companies following Prime Minister Abe's corporate reform agenda have seen benefits. From 2010 to June of this year, the index outperformed Japan's stock market index by 10%. This suggests that Abe's reforms have had a positive impact on corporate governance in Japan.
